-- BluEarth to Buy Four Canadian Solar Projects for $217 Million
-- B y   A n d r e w   H e r n d o n
-- 2013-06-05T18:46:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-05/bluearth-to-buy-four-canadian-solar-projects-for-217-million.html
BluEarth Renewables Inc., a Calgary-based independent power producer, agreed to buy four solar-power
plants from Canadian Solar Inc. for C$225 million  ($217
million).  The projects in Kawartha Lakes, Belleville, Beaverton and
Napanee, Ontario, Canada, are expected to be enter operation
next year and will have 53.9 megawatts of generating capacity,
Canadian Solar said today in a statement.  Construction will begin this year and Canadian Solar will
supply 186,000 of its solar panels. The company is based in
Guelph, Ontario, and has manufacturing facilities in  China .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Herndon in  San Francisco  at 
 aherndon2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
